<div id="review_1263457709" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1263457709" />
    <a title="Deborah Pickstone" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/37849334-deborah-pickstone"><img alt="Deborah Pickstone" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1432503842p2/37849334.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1263457709?book_show_action=true">Apr 24, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Deborah Pickstone" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Deborah Pickstone" href="/user/show/37849334-deborah-pickstone">Deborah Pickstone</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=favourite-authors">favourite-authors</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=biographical-novel">biographical-novel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=history-of-all-things">history-of-all-things</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=william-marshal">william-marshal</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=serieses-fictional">serieses-fictional</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=human-nature">human-nature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=uk-fiction">uk-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=medieval">medieval</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=re-reads">re-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/37849334-deborah-pickstone?shelf=all-time-faves">all-time-faves</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1263457709" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6142990006121592472">There is much less in the way of historical error in this book. Ms Penman&apos;s research has tightened up and become outstanding, by fiction standards and actually by historical standards - I have read less convincing historians.<br/><br/>This very comprehensively tells the story of the dysfunctional family dynamics that tore the family of Henry II and Eleanor of Aquitaine apart, the tragedy of the death of two sons and the heartrending end of Henry himself. Along the way, we also get the story of William Mar</span>
  <span id="freeText6142990006121592472" style="display:none">There is much less in the way of historical error in this book. Ms Penman's research has tightened up and become outstanding, by fiction standards and actually by historical standards - I have read less convincing historians.<br /><br />This very comprehensively tells the story of the dysfunctional family dynamics that tore the family of Henry II and Eleanor of Aquitaine apart, the tragedy of the death of two sons and the heartrending end of Henry himself. Along the way, we also get the story of William Marshal, which is a dramatic bravura performance in it's own right!<br /><br />There is not a single major character in this novel who is not well drawn and interesting. Henry II was - in my own view - one of the most interesting of the English kings. He was also, arguably, one of the most successful, despite the dire family dynamics. And, despite history's ordure throwing, John was the son most like him as King. The politics of the reign remain fascinating.<br /><br />Ms Penman is a favourite HF author of mine because even her early work is characterised by honest research and willingness to accept her own mistakes. This novel is one of her best three, in my view - the other two are the two Lionheart novels.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6142990006121592472" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


