<div id="review_38782239" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/38782239" />
    <a title="Heidi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/82251-heidi"><img alt="Heidi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1215903881p2/82251.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/38782239?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heidi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heidi" href="/user/show/82251-heidi">Heidi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82251-heidi?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82251-heidi?shelf=british-isles">british-isles</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82251-heidi?shelf=monarchy">monarchy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/82251-heidi?shelf=plantagenets">plantagenets</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer38782239" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16366405162906406804">SKP is really one of my favorite authors, but after reading Here Be Dragons, everything else falls short (When Christ and His Saints Slept is a close second). I have always appreciated her historical accuracy, but I felt like she tried to cover too much history in too few pages with this book. There were times when I found myself skimming pages to get to the plot. She took her time with Christ &amp; His Saints and the plot was more compelling, despite being much longer. There were times when I felt </span>
  <span id="freeText16366405162906406804" style="display:none">SKP is really one of my favorite authors, but after reading Here Be Dragons, everything else falls short (When Christ and His Saints Slept is a close second). I have always appreciated her historical accuracy, but I felt like she tried to cover too much history in too few pages with this book. There were times when I found myself skimming pages to get to the plot. She took her time with Christ &amp; His Saints and the plot was more compelling, despite being much longer. There were times when I felt like history took over the plot of this book, despite the fact that the full history of Henry's relationship with his sons was necessary for a true and meaningful character development.<br /><br />In all, this was still a good book and a good read, just not a favorite that I will return to again and again. Nonetheless, I'm still excited that SKP is writing "Lionhart," which is supposed to be about Eleanor, Richard, &amp; John... I assume this will bridge the gap between Devil's Brood and Here Be Dragons.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16366405162906406804" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


